# 🧠 OS Concept 2: Circuit Breaker Pattern

🔥 Very important distributed systems topic.

---

## 1️⃣ Problem

If one service keeps failing,

continuous requests worsen problem.

---

## Solution

Circuit breaker temporarily stops requests.

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

Electrical circuit breaker ⚡

Cuts power during overload.

---

## States

---

## 🔹 Closed

Normal operation.

---

## 🔹 Open

Requests blocked.

---

## 🔹 Half-open

Testing recovery.

---

## Why Useful?

✔ prevents cascading failures
✔ improves stability

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why circuit breaker pattern used?**

👉 To prevent repeated failures from overwhelming systems.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="6q1zpw"
Too many failures → stop requests temporarily
```

